SIMPLE: deafness
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Deafness
<hw>Deaf"ness</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Incapacity of perceiving sounds; the state of the organs which
prevents the impression which constitute hearing; want of the sense of
hearing.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Unwillingness to hear; voluntary rejection of what
is addressed to the understanding.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Nervous deafness</b></col>, <cd>a variety of deafness
dependent upon morbid change in some portion of the nervous system,
especially the auditory nerve.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Deal</ent>⟦br⟧
